comments: a(n) is the number of n X n (0,1) matrices with distinct rows modulo rows permutations . - Yuval Dekel (dekelyuval(AT)hotmail.com), Nov 13 2003
formula: G.f.: A(x) = Sum_{n>=0} log(1 + 2^n*x)^n / n!. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Dec 28 2007
prog: (PARI) a(n)=binomial(2^n,n)(PARI) /* G.f. A(x) as Sum of Series: */ a(n)=polcoeff(sum(k=0,n,log(1+2^k*x +x*O(x^n))^k/k!),n) \\ _Paul D. Hanna_, Dec 28 2007
